A constant can hold a fully known struct value.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    Defaults = |
        title String,
        year Int,
    |

    defaults #= Defaults("Beanstalk", 2026)
]

Read its fields during compilation or use one field in runtime code:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    page_title #= defaults.title
    io.line(defaults.title)
]

The complete const record is not an ordinary runtime object. Use its fields
instead.
